{"title_page": "Dion Leonard", "text_new": "{{short description|Australian/British ultramarathon runner}}\n[[File:Dion Leonard .jpg|thumb|Dion Leonard running the 2013 Kalahari Extreme 250km Marathon in the Kalahari Desert, South Africa]]\n'''Dion Leonard''' (born 2 January 1975) <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://statistik.d-u-v.org/getresultperson.php?runner=470359|title=DUV Ultra Marathon Statistics|website=statistik.d-u-v.org|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> is an Australian/British [[ultramarathon]] runner, motivational speaker and author of [[The New York Times Best Seller list|New York Times Bestseller]] 'Finding Gobi',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Finding-Gobi-Little-Very-Heart/dp/0718098579|title=Finding Gobi|last=|first=|date=|website=www.amazon.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>  the non fiction memoir of his story of his dog, [[Gobi (dog)|Gobi]], who ran 77 miles of a 155-mile race across the Gobi Desert.<ref>{{Citation|title=Stray dog joined extreme runner during China race - BBC News|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D2-xSMsKIMk|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> Leonard started running in 2013 and has already achieved numerous top 10 finishes (including wins) in ultra races around the world in the most extreme conditions. Leonard has not only competed in but completed some of the world's toughest \u00a0ultra running races across the most inhospitable landscapes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Dion-Leonard/e/B06XGJYCR6?ref=dbs_a_mng_rwt_scns_share|title=Dion Leonard|last=|first=|date=|website=www.amazon.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-07}}</ref>\n\n* In 2019, Leonard won the inaugural Delirious West 200 mile race in a time of 61 hours and 24 minutes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-02-25/delirious-west/10843682|title=Ultramarathon runner tackles 320km course in 61 hours with no sleep|last=Honeybone|first=Ellie|date=2019-02-25|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> Leonard also became the first man to complete the [[Grand Slam of Ultrarunning]] and the Leadville Leadman series in a single year.<ref>{{Citation|title=Grand Slam of Ultrarunning|date=2019-09-08|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Grand_Slam_of_Ultrarunning&oldid=914630173|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>\n* In 2018, Leonard completed the Triple Crown of 200 mile races, finishing the series in 2nd place overall in 220:10:44.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ultrasignup.com/results_event.aspx?did=51803|title=2018 Triple Crown of 200s 200 Miler Slam - Results|website=ultrasignup.com|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>\n* In 2017, Leonard won the 250&nbsp;km [[Kalahari Augrabies Extreme Marathon]] in a time of 26 hours and 22 minutes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kaem.co.za/kaem_results/|title=KAEM Results {{!}} Kalahari Augrabies Extreme Marathon|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>\n*In 2016, Leonard finished 2nd at the Gobi Desert 250&nbsp;km race in 29 hours and 32 minutes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ultrasignup.com/m_results_participant.aspx?fname=Dion&lname=Leonard|title=Dion Leonard's Results|website=ultrasignup.com|access-date=2019-12-18}}</ref>\n*In 2015, Leonard finished 3rd at the 220km Cambodia - The Ancient Khmer Path. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://statistik.d-u-v.org/getresultevent.php?event=25534|title=DUV Ultra Marathon Statistics|website=statistik.d-u-v.org|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n*In 2014, Leonard finished 2nd at the 250km [[Kalahari Augrabies Extreme Marathon]] in a time of 23 hours and 28 minutes. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://statistik.d-u-v.org/getresultevent.php?event=16594|title=DUV Ultra Marathon Statistics|website=statistik.d-u-v.org|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n== Media appearances ==\nLeonard has been featured on CNN, NBC Today Show, Good Morning Britain, CBS, CNBC, ABC America, Associated Press, ESPN, Pickler and Ben, CCTV, BBC Breakfast, BBC World, Le Parole Della Settimana, Good Morning Croatia, Good Morning Slovenia; Live radio interviews with BBC Radio 5 Live, BBC Outlook, Talk Sport UK, NPR America, ABC Radio Australia, Eric Zane Show. Leonard has also been interviewed across print media including China Daily, The New York Times, The Sunday Times, Washington Post, UK Independent, USA Today, Canadian Post, Corrierre della Serra, Novi List, Grazia, Variety, La Republica, The Sun, New York Post, Daily Mail, Le Monde and The Sydney Morning Herald.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.findinggobi.com/dion-leonard|title=Dion Leonard Extreme Ultra Runner|website=www.findinggobi.com|language=en|access-date=2019-11-07}}</ref>\n\n== Books ==\nIn October 2016, [[HarperCollins Publishers]] announced the expected publication of a trilogy of books about Leonard's and Gobi's journey together.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/finding-gobi-to-be-published-through-harpercollins-global-publishing-program-300342733.html|title=Finding Gobi To Be Published through HarperCollins Global Publishing Program|last=Nelson|first=Thomas|website=www.prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2019-11-07}}</ref> The book titled ''Finding Gobi'', received favourable [https://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-7180-9857-5 high praise in Publishers Weekly] and other reviews. The paperback version was officially launched in United States on 1 June 2017 and went onto become a New York Times Bestseller at number 3.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/10/15/sports/|title=Sports and Fitness Books - Best Sellers - Oct. 15, 2017 - The New York Times|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-01-03|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The hardback version was released in United Kingdom, Australia and New Zealand on 13 June 2017 reaching the Sunday Times Bestsellers list.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.harpercollins.com.au/9780008227975/finding-gobi-main-edition-the-true-story-of-a-little-dog-and-an-incredible-journey|title=Finding Gobi (Main Edition): The True Story of a Little Dog and an Incredible Journey|website=HarperCollins Australia|language=en-AU|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref> This was followed by a paperback version later released in February 2018 also reaching the Sunday Times Bestseller List.  The book for adults is now available in 20 languages: English, Spanish, Dutch, Polish, Italian, Japanese, German, Finnish, Swedish, Danish, Portuguese, Simplified Chinese, Chinese Traditional, Korean, French, Vietnamese, Hungarian, Bulgarian, Croatian and Slovene. A young adult edition and children's picture book was also released in 2017. On 13 March 2017, Twentieth Century Fox announced that it is developing a movie based on Dion Leonard and Gobi's extensive journey together.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/finding-gobi-movie-fox-dion-leonard-book-1202007592/|title=Dion Leonard\u2019s Memoir About Stray Dog to Get Movie Adaptation at Fox (EXCLUSIVE)|last=McNary|first=Dave|date=2017-03-13|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-11-07}}</ref>\n\n*Finding Gobi: A Little Dog with a Very Big Heart, (HarperCollins) June 2017. {{ISBN|978-0718098575}}\n* Finding Gobi: Young Reader's Edition: The True Story of One Little Dog's Big Journey, (Thomas Nelson) August 2017. {{ISBN|978-0718075316}}\n* Gobi: A Little Dog with a Big Heart (picture book), (Thomas Nelson) August 2017. {{ISBN|978-0718075293}}\n* Finding Gobi for Little Ones (board book), (Thomas Nelson) March 2018. {{ISBN|978-0718075309}}\n* Lara The Runaway Cat: How One Cat Travelled the World to Discover Home is Where the Heart is, (HarperElement) February 2019. {{ISBN|978-0008316181}}\n\nLeonard has also written in:\n\n* Beastly Journeys: Unusual Tales of Travel with Animals (Bradt Travel Guides), June 2018. {{ISBN|978-1784770815}}\n* Test Your Dog: Is Your Dog an Undiscovered Genius? (HarperCollins) September 2018. {{ISBN|978-0008149659}}\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.dionleonard.com Official Website]\n* https://www.findinggobi.com/dion-leonard\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leonard, Dion}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male ultramarathon runners]]\n[[Category:Australian ultramarathon runners]]\n[[Category:Warwick, Queensland]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Australian/British ultramarathon runner}}\n[[File:Dion Leonard .jpg|thumb|Dion Leonard running the 2013 Kalahari Extreme 250km Marathon in the Kalahari Desert, South Africa]]\n'''Dion Leonard''' (born 2 January 1975) <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://statistik.d-u-v.org/getresultperson.php?runner=470359|title=DUV Ultra Marathon Statistics|website=statistik.d-u-v.org|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> is an Australian/British [[ultramarathon]] runner, motivational speaker and author of [[The New York Times Best Seller list|New York Times Bestseller]] 'Finding Gobi',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Finding-Gobi-Little-Very-Heart/dp/0718098579|title=Finding Gobi|last=|first=|date=|website=www.amazon.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>  the non fiction memoir of his story of his dog, [[Gobi (dog)|Gobi]], who ran 77 miles of a 155-mile race across the Gobi Desert.<ref>{{Citation|title=Stray dog joined extreme runner during China race - BBC News|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D2-xSMsKIMk|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> Leonard started running in 2013 and has already achieved numerous top 10 finishes (including wins) in ultra races around the world in the most extreme conditions. Leonard has not only competed in but completed some of the world's toughest \u00a0ultra running races across the most inhospitable landscapes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Dion-Leonard/e/B06XGJYCR6?ref=dbs_a_mng_rwt_scns_share|title=Dion Leonard|last=|first=|date=|website=www.amazon.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-07}}</ref>\n\n* In 2019, Leonar